<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,319,847]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[201,430,427,452]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,316,427,452]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(female).
</emphasis>
Gnathopod 1 basis anteroproximally expanded; propodus narrowing distally; dactylus very short. Gnathopod 2 basis distally expanded; carpus distally truncate; propodus palm concave with three to four major tubercles. Pereopods 5–7 bases narrowly expanded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,319,847]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,263,536,560]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Note.</emphasis>
Ledoyer’s (1979, 1986) descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1965" box="[748,918,536,560]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Leucothoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micronesiae">
<emphasis box="[748,918,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. micronesiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show discrepancies with Barnard’s original description. Ledoyer illustrates scattered ocelli and wider or more narrow bases on pereopods 5–7. The material used in these descriptions needs to be examined to determine if it is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1965" box="[914,1079,608,632]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Leucothoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micronesiae">
<emphasis box="[914,1079,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">L. micronesiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a different species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,319,847]" box="[201,755,644,668]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,262,644,668]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<collectingRegion box="[201,262,644,668]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Male</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
(sexually dimorphic characters). Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,319,847]" box="[201,577,679,704]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
